# UX/UI Design System

Every interface must feel modern, calm, premium, clear, responsive and accessible.

Prefer:
- strong visual hierarchy;
- generous spacing;
- readable typography;
- clear CTAs;
- subtle borders and shadows;
- rounded corners;
- consistent states;
- mobile-first layouts.

Avoid:
- crowded screens;
- weak contrast;
- unclear labels;
- inconsistent spacing;
- too many colors;
- generic admin UI when a better SaaS UI is possible.

Every UI task must check:
- default, hover, focus-visible, active, disabled states;
- loading, empty, error and success states;
- accessibility and keyboard navigation;
- responsive behavior;
- clarity of the primary action.
